AGI - "I'm very sorry. This unilateral choice that yesterday took Giuseppe Conte with the Five Stars without looking together a solution. I want to say it clearly: so they help the right. We need a policy that looks more at the next generations, than at the next elections and polls of the last days and the next days."
He told Bari the secretary of the Pd, Elly Schlein, from the stage of "Let's go!" in support of the mayor Vito Leccese, supported by the dems, commenting on the choice of the leader of the Movement Five Stars, Giuseppe Conte, to parade from the primaries of the centerleft in Bari on Sunday 7 April.
<div </div
&nbsp;
"I understand that those who started to make politics directly from Palazzo Chigi may not have so much familiarity with the basic militancy that you represent and with the effort to build collective democratic paths, like those who mount the gazebos of the primaries - he said turning to the square -. But I claim to have at least respect for this collective effort and for this community. To blow up the primary, three days from the vote is a sberla for all people well that he was preparing Sunday to come to vote for Vito or Michele (Laforgia, ndr)". And he concluded: "It is also an unbearable misrepresentation that the two candidates, both mirrored people, could use untransparent methods without being able to control the vote coming."
<div </div
&nbsp;
"Our line must be very clear: We do not accept and do not want dirty votes and votes bought. We don't care. We want them away." He said the secretary of the Pd, Elly Schlein, from the stage of "Let's go!", commenting on yesterday's poll in Bari.
&nbsp;
<div </div "The story of yesterday, of Triggiano, and the investigations of the exchange vote, if the accusations are confirmed, are very serious - the secretary continued -. And first of all they hurt those who commit themselves every day to return dignity to politics in a country where 50% of the electricians and voters stopped voting. In front of these facts the solution is not the easiest, point your finger at someone else, someone outside of themselves, but look inside. And the democratic party intends to do it all the way. He intends to do it with self-critical and determination. Because we are not immune to attempts at infiltration, but we must together become it: never allow such things to happen." And concludes: "It is not denying the participation that contrasts infiltration. It is not denying more democracy that the space of those who want to condition it is contrasted. That's the opposite."
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
&nbsp;

