&nbsp;
First, there is concern for the crisis of nearby Sahel, after military strikes in Mali, Burkina Faso and Niger. An unstable area for the presence of jihadist forces and on which Russia seems to nurture strong interests. This is why Mattarella, in the joint declarations, points out that Italy is at the side of Ghana and the African democracies, a model for stabilizing the area. Several fronts around which Rome and Accra intend to increase cooperation: the economic sector, but also the cultural sector - the presidents explain - in addition to that of security in contrast to illegal immigration and the phenomenon of piracy in the Gulf of Guinea.
&nbsp;
"Ghana was the leader of independence against colonialism and this deserved the sympathy of Italy's closeness," says Mattarella, in greeting to delegations. "I thank you for quoting Enrico Mattei," he adds. "The choice of the name of Mattei for the plan that the Italian government has launched is not random - clarifies - and it is because Mattei was a friend of Ghana, West Africa and the African continent against all forms of colonial exploitation" in favor of a "colaboration on the equal and protection of local resources, and this is the objective of the Mattei plan that wants to be of collaboration according to the indications, the needs and various proposals defined by the governments of the continent. The Mattei plan, the president insists, recalls "a protagonist of the friendship between Africa and Europe and the independence of Africa". Mattarella talks about immigration. "It is necessary to address together the migration phenomenon that must be converted, from a disorderly phenomenon, managed by traffickers of human beings, to a phenomenon with legally defined inputs - he states -. It's an important goal."
<div </div
&nbsp;
"I want to reassure President Sergio Mattarella that Ghana will cooperate in the elimination of illegal immigration, in the fight against terrorism, in contrast to the effects of climate change," Akufo-Addo says. "I want to reiterate the friendship that binds us, which is a solid friendship," says Mattarella. "Together we are for multilateralism, for a world marked by dialogue, confrontation, collaboration and not opposition. Much more in this period of turbulence and serious crisis we must reiterate that the perspective of humanity is not that, it is dialogue, collaboration between countries and that in Europe, Africa and the Middle East, the path of war is wrong". It is necessary, continued, "to work for a strengthening of the United Nations. The challenges we face, like humanity, especially with regard to climate, require great international collaboration. They are impossible in contrast."
<h2> "Measures for multilateralism"
<
<span><img><img height="15" title="Click and drag to move" width="15"></span></span>" Italy considers Ghana as a virtuous example of democracy, a model for other countries. With democratic rooting it offers a model for the whole region. Ghana and Italy are linked by a very strong friendship. We have emphasized with great vigor how Ghana - he adds - is a fundamental partner in the partnership between the EU and Africa, a relationship that is based on mutual respect". The Italian President then assures that "I stop Italy's commitment to piracy in the Gulf of Guinea, where we participate with a military ship for the security of freedom of navigation". Tomorrow, before you leave, you will visit the Bettica ship, engaged in a three-month mission in the area. At the presidential jubilee house, Mattarella wishes to his colleague from Ghana for his 80 years, just completed. I've reached the finish line, "any back door", remembers the president. Following the deposition of a crown and the visit of the museum entitled to former Ghanaian President Kwame Nkrumah. And, in the afternoon, the visit to Fort Christiansborg, a castle built by the Danes who over the years was also used as a collection point for slaves departing from Ghana.
</div
